# SOLAT README & Onboarding Agent (7.2 rule)

When editing [README.md](README.md) or [.env.example](.env.example), keep the following in sync so new devs and Cursor can run the project without guessing.

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.11+ with [uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv)
- Node.js 18+ with [pnpm](https://pnpm.io)
- Rust (for Tauri) — [rustup](https://rustup.rs)

## Quick start

- Copy .env.example to .env; fill IG credentials if using broker features.
- Run `./scripts/dev.sh` to start engine + Tauri UI (or `pnpm dev:engine` and `pnpm dev:ui` separately).
- Engine: http://127.0.0.1:8765; Tauri dev server: port 1420.

